nce with, and policies towards, direct foreign investment in the Asian-Pacific region. Of particular interest are the discussion of investment within and from Japan and the synthesis of studies on North America, Australia, and the developing Asian countries. The book is a valuable guide for policy-makers and businessmen, and should serve as an essential text for students of foreign investment. General readers will find answers here to many questions on the economics of countries which encourage foreign investment or invest considerably outside their own shores.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 4aDISCOUNT-B. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / International / Economics.2bisacsh1 aBrash, Donald T., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDrysdale, Peter, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aHamada, Koichi, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHughes, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHymer, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJohnson, Harry G., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKindleberger, Charles P., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKomiya, Ryutaro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPerkins, J.O.N., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSadli, Mohammad, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSafarian, A. E., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aVirata, Cesar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aViravan, Amnuay, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWionczek, Miguel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabular